+### Build Notes (Vendored + SIMDe)
+
+This repository includes local (vendored) copies of:
+
+- `boost_1_78_0`
+- `htslib-1.16`
+- `phase/src/simde`
+
+The current build setup was updated with the following goals:
+
+- remove hard dependency on Intel-only AVX2/FMA compilation flags in `phase`
+- enable SIMD portability through SIMDe headers in `phase/src/models`
+- make default builds resolve Boost/HTSlib from vendored paths
+- align Docker build behavior with local `make -f makefile`
+
+Practical implications:
+
+- `phase` now includes SIMDe headers (`simde/x86/avx2.h`, `simde/x86/fma.h`) with native aliases enabled.
+- Top-level `make -f makefile` bootstraps required vendored dependency artifacts when missing:
+  - Boost staged static libraries (`boost_1_78_0/stage/lib/libboost_{iostreams,program_options,serialization}.a`)
+  - HTSlib static library (`htslib-1.16/libhts.a`)
+- Top-level build now also copies final executables into the repository-level `bin/` folder.
+- Dockerfile uses vendored sources from the repository and invokes the root makefile (`make -f makefile`).
+
+Notes:
+
+- This change improves portability (including non-x86 targets) for `phase` SIMD code paths by relying on SIMDe compatibility layers.
+- Link-time dependencies such as `curl`, `crypto`, `deflate`, `z`, `bz2`, and `lzma` are still required by project link flags / HTSlib linkage.
